description: Enforce core/UI boundary and TDD for src/core changes
globs: src/core/**,tests/core/**
alwaysApply: false
---

# Core boundary

- `src/core/**` must **never** import `react`, `react-dom`, or any React subpath.
- Core code is pure TypeScript. No JSX, no hooks, no DOM APIs unless wrapped for testability.
- ESLint `no-restricted-imports` enforces this — do not disable without an ADR update.

## TDD required for core changes

1. Write or update Vitest tests first (Red).
2. Implement minimal code (Green).
3. Refactor without changing behavior.

Fixtures: `tests/fixtures/` — examples derived from `docs/spec/supported_types.md`.

## Module layout

- `src/core/yaml/` — parse, serialize, validate
- `src/core/schema/` — Zod types from spec
- `src/core/templates/` — scan + evaluate
- `src/core/assets/` — scanner + resolver
- `src/core/renderer/` — canvas, colors, dither, element renderers

UI code in `src/ui/` calls core via `src/core/index.ts` exports only. ESLint enforces this on `src/ui/**` and `tests/ui/**` (for `src/core/*` subpaths).
